<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-09-17T08:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-09-17T08:32:00-05:00" n="49" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4 A 2/92: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                        Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-17T09:00:00-04:32"><hi rend="italic">September 17,
                                        1924—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:35
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>28. Department’s telegram no. 19, September 11, 10 p.m.<note n="84" xml:id="d49fn84">See footnote 81, <ref target="#pg_98">p.
                                98</ref>.</note> Foreign Office informs me delegate has been
                            appointed to opium conference but impossible to restrict cultivation of
                            coca leaf plant. Full report by mail.<note n="85" xml:id="d49fn85">Not
                                printed.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cottrell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>